\f0\fs24 \cf0 # iFoundIt B2B Schools Portal \'97 MVP Project Plan\
\
## Project Context\
\
iFoundIt is a lost-and-found recovery platform. The existing B2C product (built on Wix + Velo) allows consumers to tag personal items with NFC tags and get notified when a finder taps them. This project builds a separate B2B system for UK secondary schools, enabling schools to tag student phone pouches (mag-lock pouches mandated under the Children's Wellbeing and Schools Act 2026) and recover them when lost \'97 via iFoundIt's existing public finder network.\
\
**The core problem being solved:** All YONDR/mag-lock pouches look identical. Students carry them everywhere. When lost in public, there is no way for a finder to know who the pouch belongs to or how to return it. The iFoundIt NFC tag on the pouch, when tapped by a finder, anonymously notifies the school without exposing student details.\
\
**The B2B system is completely separate from the B2C Wix/Velo system.** School-registered tags use a different NFC URL (`schools.ifoundit.io/find/[serial]`) pre-programmed before shipping. The two systems share no database. The only shared asset is the iFoundIt brand and finder network.\
\
