## Data Models\
\
Run the following in Supabase SQL editor to create the schema.\
\
```sql\
-- Schools / organisations\
CREATE TABLE organisations (\
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),\
  name TEXT NOT NULL,\
  slug TEXT UNIQUE NOT NULL,           -- e.g. 'st-marys-coventry'\
  address TEXT,\
  contact_email TEXT NOT NULL,         -- where found notifications are sent\
  contact_phone TEXT,\
  logo_url TEXT,\
  subscription_tier TEXT DEFAULT 'pilot', -- 'pilot' | 'standard' | 'mat'\
  active BOOLEAN DEFAULT true,\
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\
  updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()\
);\
\
-- Students (PII - handle carefully under UK GDPR)\
CREATE TABLE students (\
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),\
  organisation_id UUID REFERENCES organisations(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\
  first_name TEXT NOT NULL,\
  last_name TEXT NOT NULL,\
  year_group TEXT,\
  form_group TEXT,\
  parent_email TEXT,                   -- optional, for future parent notifications\
  parent_phone TEXT,                   -- optional\
  active BOOLEAN DEFAULT true,\
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\
  updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()\
);\
\
-- Tags (NFC serial numbers provisioned by iFoundIt before shipping)\
CREATE TABLE tags (\
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),\
  serial_number TEXT UNIQUE NOT NULL,  -- matches NFC chip serial, used in URL\
  organisation_id UUID REFERENCES organisations(id),\
  student_id UUID REFERENCES students(id),\
  activated_at TIMESTAMPTZ,\
  active BOOLEAN DEFAULT false,\
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\
  updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()\
);\
\
-- Recovery events (when a finder taps a tag)\
CREATE TABLE found_events (\
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),\
  tag_id UUID REFERENCES tags(id),\
  serial_number TEXT NOT NULL,         -- denormalised for fast lookup\
  finder_email TEXT,\
  finder_phone TEXT,\
  finder_message TEXT,\
  location_description TEXT,\
  notification_sent_at TIMESTAMPTZ,\
  resolved_at TIMESTAMPTZ,\
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()\
);\
\
-- School admin users (extends Supabase auth.users)\
CREATE TABLE admin_users (\
  id UUID REFERENCES auth.users(id) PRIMARY KEY,\
  organisation_id UUID REFERENCES organisations(id),\
  role TEXT DEFAULT 'school_admin',    -- 'school_admin' | 'ifoundit_superadmin'\
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()\
);\
```\
\
### Row-Level Security (RLS)\
\
Enable RLS on all tables. School admins can only read/write rows where `organisation_id` matches their own. iFoundIt superadmins can access all rows.\
\
```sql\
-- Example RLS policy for students table\
ALTER TABLE students ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;\
\
CREATE POLICY "School admins can manage their own students"\
ON students\
FOR ALL\
USING (\
  organisation_id = (\
    SELECT organisation_id FROM admin_users WHERE id = auth.uid()\
  )\
);\
```\
\
Apply equivalent policies to `tags` and `found_events`.\
\
