## Epic 4 \'97 GDPR-Safe Finder Page + Notification Flow\
\
### Overview\
This is the public-facing side of the system. When a member of the public finds a tagged pouch and taps it with their phone, they land on a page that tells them it belongs to a student at a named school, gives them the school's contact details, and offers a one-click "Notify the school" button. The student's name is never shown to the finder.\
\
### Finder Page: `GET /find/[serial]`\
\
**Logic:**\
1. Look up `serial` in `tags` table\
2. If not found: show "This tag isn't registered \'97 please contact iFoundIt"\
3. If found and `active = false`: show "This tag is no longer active"\
4. If found and `active = true`: look up `organisation` via `organisation_id`\
5. Render school-safe finder page\
\
**School-safe finder page content:**\
```\
[School Logo if available]\
\
You've found something that belongs to a student at:\
[School Name]\
\
The item is securely locked and the student cannot access it without a key held at the school.\
\
To return this item, you can:\
\'95 Contact the school directly: [contact_phone]\
\'95 Click below to notify the school instantly \'97 no account needed\
\
[NOTIFY THE SCHOOL] \uc0\u8592  primary CTA button\
\
Thank you for your honesty.\
```\
\
**What is NOT shown to the finder:**\
- Student name\
- Student year group or form\
- Parent contact details\
- Any personally identifiable information\
\
### Found Event Submission: `POST /api/found/[serial]`\
\
Triggered when finder clicks "Notify the school."\
\
**Input (from a short optional form shown after clicking the button):**\
```typescript\
\{\
  finder_email?: string       // optional, for school to arrange collection\
  finder_phone?: string       // optional\
  finder_message?: string     // optional free text\
  location_description?: string // e.g. "on the 47 bus, Coventry"\
\}\
```\
\
**Actions:**\
1. Look up tag by serial, get `organisation_id`, `student_id`\
2. Insert row into `found_events`\
3. Look up student name (for internal notification only)\
4. Look up `organisation.contact_email`\
5. Send email to school via Resend (see template below)\
6. Send confirmation page to finder\
7. Update `found_events.notification_sent_at = now()`\
\
**Email to school \'97 template:**\
\
```\
Subject: iFoundIt \'97 A student's pouch has been found\
\
A phone pouch registered to one of your students has been found.\
\
Student: [First Name] [Last Name] ([Year Group], [Form Group])\
Tag serial: [serial_number]\
Found at: [location_description or "Location not provided"]\
Time: [timestamp]\
\
Finder contact:\
Email: [finder_email or "Not provided"]\
Phone: [finder_phone or "Not provided"]\
Message: [finder_message or "No message"]\
\
Log in to your iFoundIt school portal to mark this as resolved:\
https://schools.ifoundit.io/events\
\
\'97\
iFoundIt School Recovery System\
```\
\
**Confirmation page shown to finder (`/found/success`):**\
```\
Thank you \'97 [School Name] has been notified.\
\
They will be in touch if they need to arrange collection.\
You're helping keep students' belongings safe.\
```\
\
### Acceptance Criteria\
- [ ] Finder page loads in under 2 seconds with no authentication required\
- [ ] Finder page never displays student name, year group, form, or any PII\
- [ ] School receives notification email within 60 seconds of finder submission\
- [ ] Found event appears in school admin's `/events` log immediately\
- [ ] Submitting the found form twice for the same tag within 1 hour is blocked (debounce) to prevent notification spam\
- [ ] If tag serial is unrecognised, finder sees a helpful error, not a crash\
