## Key Decisions and Notes for Development\
\
**Authentication approach:** Use Supabase Auth with the `@supabase/ssr` package (not the legacy `auth-helpers`). Session is stored in cookies, readable server-side in Next.js Server Components and Route Handlers. See Supabase docs: [Server-Side Auth for Next.js](https://supabase.com/docs/guides/auth/server-side/nextjs).\
\
**Middleware:** `middleware.ts` should check for a valid Supabase session on all `/dashboard`, `/students`, `/tags`, `/events`, `/settings`, and `/admin` routes. Redirect to `/login` if not authenticated.\
\
**Role checking:** After confirming auth, check `admin_users.role` from the database. If role is `school_admin`, restrict access to their `organisation_id` only (enforced by RLS). If role is `ifoundit_superadmin`, allow access to all `/admin` routes.\
\
**Finder page is fully public:** No auth, no session check. It must be fast and work on mobile. Keep it under 50KB total. No unnecessary JavaScript.\
\
**Email deliverability:** Configure Resend with the `schools.ifoundit.io` domain. Send from `noreply@schools.ifoundit.io`. Include school name in the From display name (e.g. "iFoundIt School Recovery"). This avoids spam filters.\
\
**GDPR:** Before going live, complete a Data Protection Impact Assessment (DPIA) using the ICO template. Ensure privacy policy at `schools.ifoundit.io/privacy` covers school data processing. Data Processing Agreements with each school must be signed before pilot launch \'97 store signed copies.\
\
**NFC tag URL format:** Tags shipped to schools are pre-programmed with `https://schools.ifoundit.io/find/SERIALNUMBER`. Serial numbers should be alphanumeric, 8 characters minimum, uppercase (e.g. `A3F9B2C1`). Do not use special characters in serial numbers as they appear in URLs.\
